"from":{"fname":"ee.hw.solar-charging","id":"2torquuzh3kpr666gisn7ir","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ee.hw.solar-charging","alias":"Power Path using a P-channel MOSFET","position":{"start":{"line":32,"column":210,"offset":2330},"end":{"line":32,"column":306,"offset":2426},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"sameFile":false,"to":{"fname":"ee.hw.solar-charging","anchorHeader":"power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet"}},{"type":"ref","from":{"fname":"ee.hw.solar-charging","id":"2torquuzh3kpr666gisn7ir","vaultName":"vault"},"value":"ee.hw.mcp73837-li-ion-battery-charger","position":{"start":{"line":16,"column":5,"offset":799},"end":{"line":16,"column":81,"offset":875},"indent":[]},"xvault":false,"to":{"fname":"ee.hw.mcp73837-li-ion-battery-charger","anchorHeader":"application-note"}}],"anchors":{"power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet":{"type":"header","text":"Power Path using a P-channel MOSFET","value":"power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet","line":8,"column":0,"depth":2},"related-discussions":{"type":"header","text":"Related Discussions","value":"related-discussions","line":24,"column":0,"depth":2},"solar-calculations":{"type":"header","text":"Solar Calculations","value":"solar-calculations","line":42,"column":0,"depth":2},"to-continue-with":{"type":"header","text":"To Continue With","value":"to-continue-with","line":47,"column":0,"depth":2}},"children":[],"parent":"eokZg0xaKzp1IoIromHio","data":{}},"body":"<h1 id=\"solar-charging\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#solar-charging\"></a>Solar Charging</h1>\n<h2 id=\"power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet\"></a>Power Path using a P-channel MOSFET</h2>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/notes/cihpci1uhdkswoei2pu6ht3\">Tp4056</a> and <a href=\"/notes/notes/n2m9hj5eodzgd3omblt60v3\">dw01A</a> with power path using <a href=\"/notes/notes/q6zby7krsn4k59hz9w7gb20\">Fqp27p06</a>.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Solar panel voltage present results in power supplied to MCU via solar panel only + battery continues charging</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-05-21-17-04-01.png\"></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=37kGva3NW8w\">#383 Cheap and simple Solar Power for our small Projects (ESP32, ESP8266, Arduino)</a></li>\n</ul>\n<ul>\n<li>Discussion on when the solar voltage is somewhere between 0-5V, where the P-channel mosfet is still on\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.eevblog.com/forum/projects/solar-powered-lipo-charger-with-power-path/\">Solar powered LIPO charger with power path - Page 1</a></li>\n<li>Andreas Spiess design is almost identical to that shown in the <a href=\"/notes/notes/dk27p52krpjuf4cic0p61z4\">Mcp73837 Li Ion Battery Charger</a> application note</li>\n<li><p></p><div class=\"portal-container\">\n<div class=\"portal-head\">\n<div class=\"portal-backlink\">\n<div class=\"portal-title\">From <span class=\"portal-text-title\">Mcp73837 Li Ion Battery Charger</span></div>\n<a href=\"/notes/notes/dk27p52krpjuf4cic0p61z4\" class=\"portal-arrow\">Go to text <span class=\"right-arrow\">→</span></a>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"portal-parent-anchor\" class=\"portal-parent\" markdown=\"1\">\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-top\"></div>\n<div class=\"portal-parent-fader-bottom\"></div><h2 id=\"application-note\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#application-note\"></a>Application Note</h2>\n<ul>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-05-21-21-56-34.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-05-21-22-01-07.png\"></li>\n<li><img src=\"/notes/assets/images/2022-05-21-22-01-20.png\"></li>\n<li>Source: <a href=\"http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/appnotes/01149c.pdf\">http://ww1.microchip.com/downloads/en/appnotes/01149c.pdf</a></li>\n<li>The an1149 datasheet also has some good information on why the load should not be connected directly to the battery</li>\n</ul>\n</div></div><p></p></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"related-discussions\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#related-discussions\"></a>Related Discussions</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AskElectronics/comments/kgujq9/methods_for_charging_and_load_sharing_between/\">r/AskElectronics - Methods for charging and load sharing between solar panels and li-ion batteries?</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://forum.arduino.cc/t/help-with-li-ion-solar-charging-with-load-sharing/655618\">Help with li-ion solar charging with load-sharing</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.reddit.com/r/AskElectronics/comments/po8q3c/looking_for_an_iccircuit_that_would_allow_me_to/\">r/AskElectronics - Looking for an IC/circuit that would allow me to safely charge a lipo battery that is still connected to a device (like a cellphone)</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Anything that lists 1) powerpath, 2) Vsys output, or 3) uses an external current sense resistor should work fine - so BQ25606, CN3791, STNS01 (if your phone's current draw is unusually low), but not TP4056 or MCP738xx.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/notes/80buocd0itxhhon5qj54imz\">Cn3791 Solar Mppt Approx Charger</a> (for solar with MPPT approximation)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/notes/f661zk2c5a4pwwzmfnckxge\">Bq25606 Buck Lipo Battery Charger</a> (not specifically for solar or MPPT like)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"/notes/notes/m6mqzgu5akj411t41ir4ly0\">Stns01 Li Ion Linear Battery Charger with Ldo</a> - Package and LDO make it unsuitable for my needs as the <a href=\"/notes/notes/kWFdZQuRbvz7uwXfqCA8n\">Nrf52840</a> has an inbuilt DC converter so regulating twice would be inefficient</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Although <a href=\"/notes/notes/cihpci1uhdkswoei2pu6ht3\">Tp4056</a> and <a href=\"/notes/notes/dk27p52krpjuf4cic0p61z4\">Mcp73837 Li Ion Battery Charger</a> do not have an external current sense resistor, a power path can be created used the application not for the MCP73837 mentioned in <a href=\"/notes/notes/2torquuzh3kpr666gisn7ir#power-path-using-a-p-channel-mosfet\">Power Path using a P-channel MOSFET</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<blockquote>\n<p>The reason for these precautions is that lithum-ion batteries do not like being float-charged (held at 4.2v while current asymptotes to zero) as it causes them to grow dendrites and stab themselves to a fiery death.</p>\n</blockquote>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2 id=\"solar-calculations\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#solar-calculations\"></a>Solar Calculations</h2>\n<p><a href=\"http://www.solarelectricityhandbook.com/solar-irradiance.html\">Solar Irradiance Calculator</a>\n<a href=\"https://solargis.com/maps-and-gis-data/download/australia\">Solar resource maps of Australia</a></p>\n<h2 id=\"to-continue-with\"><a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"anchor-heading icon-link\" href=\"#to-continue-with\"></a>To Continue With</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Great Scott video <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sU-hSFFwSmo&#x26;t=2s\">Electronic Basics #29: Solar Panel and Charge Controller</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A final year EE project</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Oz_6qOgm4-g\">My Final Year Project: NiMH Solar Battery Charger</a>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/hadefuwa/solar-charger-arduino-nano-v3/blob/06923ca40dcb1bf5046b793ef778ebeff19c3275/schematic.png\">solar-charger-arduino-nano-v3/schematic.png at 06923ca40dcb1bf5046b793ef778ebeff19c3275 · hadefuwa/solar-charger-arduino-nano-v3</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Google sheet with solar battery chargers <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/spreadsheets/d/1LVohmn0nc7Ttsbt9npN3JESeZj8wxoR_L95ZPLOyowU/edit#gid=0\">SolarBatteryChargers</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Unsure where I found this...</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>","noteIndex":{"id":"wn8PE1RhG0znK1alrGFYv","title":"Welcome","desc":"","updated":1647739693733,"created":1631901573363,"custom":{"